title: State police investigate shooting on I-495 in Wrentham - Massachusetts news
text:
WRENTHAM, Mass. (AP) — State police are investigating a late-night shooting on Interstate 495 in Wrentham.
A department spokesman says just before 11 p.m. Tuesday a southbound motorist reported that his car had been struck by gunfire. The driver was not injured.
 Troopers located apparent evidence if gunfire on the vehicle. The preliminary investigation suggests the car was not randomly targeted and a second vehicle was involved.
The investigation is ongoing.
The motorist’s name was not made public.
